This paper deals with machine learning methods for predicting set-valued outputs, which is a problem that can arise in a variety of subfields within computer science. However, given the focus on probabilistic learning methods and the use of regularization, it seems most likely that this paper would be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other possible sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as these fields may also involve predicting sets or sequences of labels.
